        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Chat Overview",
            Slug = "chat-overview",
            Summary = "An overview of the built-in chat system: direct messages, channels grouped under teams, threads, @mentions and record links, file sharing, announcements, channel roles, and real-time delivery via SignalR.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 30,
            AppRoutes = """["/chat"]""",
            Tags = """["chat","communication"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Chat Overview\n\nQB Engineer includes a built-in, real-time messaging system for internal communication. It supports one-on-one direct messages, shared channels grouped under teams, threaded replies, links to records, file attachments, and company announcements. Open it full-page at /chat or as a slide-out panel from the chat icon in the header — the header icon shows your total unread count. You can also **pop chat out into its own window** so it stays open beside whatever else you are working on.\n\n### Direct Messages\n\nA direct message (DM) is a private 1:1 conversation with one colleague. They appear in the **Direct Messages** section of the sidebar. Click **New Message** (+), search for a person by name, and start typing. Messages deliver instantly via SignalR — no refresh needed.\n\n### Channels\n\nA channel is a shared, multi-person conversation. Channels appear in the **Channels** section and come in several types: a **Group** channel you create for a topic, a **Department** channel, a **Custom** channel, a read-only **Broadcast** (announcement) channel, and **System** channels created automatically. Click **New Group** to create one (name, type, description, members), or **Browse Channels** to discover and join existing channels.\n\n### Teams\n\nA **Team** groups related channels under one collapsible heading in the sidebar (for example, an Engineering team with its own set of channels). Team channels are created automatically for a team and listed together so members can find them quickly.\n\n### Threads\n\nAny message can start a thread. Click **Reply in thread** on a message to open the thread panel on the right and reply without cluttering the main conversation. A message with replies shows a **“N replies”** link that reopens the thread.\n\n### Pop Out Into a Separate Window\n\nWhen chat is open as the slide-out panel (not the full /chat page), the header shows an **Open in window** button (the open_in_new icon). Click it to pop chat out into its own dedicated browser window that you can move to a second monitor and keep visible while you work elsewhere in the app. While the popout is open, the slide-out panel shows a **“Chat is open in a separate window”** banner and the header button changes to **Focus window** (the launch icon) — clicking it brings the popout window to the front. From that point on, clicking a DM or channel in the slide-out opens it in the popout window rather than the panel. Closing the popout window returns chat to the normal slide-out behavior. (Only one popout window exists at a time; opening again just focuses the existing one.)\n\n### Record Links\n\nMessages can contain links to records — a job, part, purchase order, sales order, quote, and more. A record link renders inline as a clickable colored chip that opens the relevant detail dialog. (Record links and @mentions arrive on messages from elsewhere in the system; the live message composer is a plain text box — there is not yet an @ picker in the box itself, so do not expect a mention/record popover while typing a chat message.)\n\n### File Attachments\n\nAttach a file (PDF, image, office document, or an engineering drawing such as STEP/STL/DXF) up to 10 MB using the paperclip button. The file uploads, previews in the composer, and sends with your next message. (File attach is available on channels.)\n\n### Announcements\n\n**Announcements** are posted by admins and managers and are delivered in real time, surfacing alongside chat and in read-only **Broadcast** channels. An announcement can be scoped company-wide, to a department, or to specific teams; carries a severity (Info, Warning, or Critical); can require acknowledgment; can expire; and can be created from reusable templates. Note that you **author** an announcement from **Admin > Announcements** (the admin Announcements panel), not from inside the chat panel — chat is where announcements are *received and read*. Broadcast channels are read-only, so only admins and managers can post to them.\n\n### Channel Roles\n\nEach channel member has a role: **Member** (read and post), **Admin** (edit the channel and manage it), or **Owner** (full control, including delete). Roles are shown in the channel settings dialog.\n\n### Unread, Read-State & Mute\n\nEach DM and channel row shows an unread badge, and the header chat icon shows your total unread count. Opening a conversation automatically marks its messages as read. **Mute** a noisy channel from its row to silence its notifications without leaving it.\n\n### Real-Time Delivery (SignalR)\n\nAll messages, replies, and announcements are delivered instantly through the **ChatHub** SignalR connection at /hubs/chat. The connection is established at login and reconnects automatically with exponential backoff if interrupted.","sections":[]}"""
        });
